Empty.description: A generic empty message that you can re-use to avoid defining duplicated empty messages in your APIs. A typical example is to use it as the request or the response type of an API method. For instance: service Foo { rpc Bar(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.protobuf.Empty); }

enumDescriptions: Backfill job was never started for the stream object (stream has backfill strategy defined as manual or object was explicitly excluded from automatic backfill).
Backfill job will start pending available resources.
Backfill job stopped (next job run will start from beginning).
Backfill job failed (due to an error).
Backfill job failed since the table structure is currently unsupported for backfill.

errors.description: Output only. Errors which caused the backfill job to fail.

lastEndTime.description: Output only. Backfill job's end time.

lastStartTime.description: Output only. Backfill job's start time.

enumDescriptions: Object backfill job was triggered automatically according to the stream's backfill strategy.
Object backfill job was triggered manually using the dedicated API.

BackfillJob.description: Represents a backfill job on a specific stream object.

message.description: A message containing more information about the error that occurred.

reason.description: A title that explains the reason for the error.

errorUuid.description: A unique identifier for this specific error, allowing it to be traced throughout the system in logs and API responses.

errorTime.description: The time when the error occurred.

StartBackfillJobRequest.description: Request for manually initiating a backfill job for a specific stream object.

additionalProperties.description: Properties of the object. Contains field @type with type URL.

metadata.description: Service-specific metadata. For example the available capacity at the given location.

name.description: Resource name for the location, which may vary between implementations. For example: `"projects/example-project/locations/us-east1"`

labels.description: Cross-service attributes for the location. For example {"cloud.googleapis.com/region": "us-east1"}

locationId.description: The canonical id for this location. For example: `"us-east1"`.

displayName.description: The friendly name for this location, typically a nearby city name. For example, "Tokyo".

Location.description: A resource that represents Google Cloud Platform location.

VpcPeeringConfig.description: The VPC Peering configuration is used to create VPC peering between Datastream and the consumer's VPC.

subnet.description: Required. A free subnet for peering. (CIDR of /29)

vpc.description: Required. Fully qualified name of the VPC that Datastream will peer to. Format: `projects/{project}/global/{networks}/{name}`

fileRotationInterval.description: The maximum duration for which new events are added before a file is closed and a new file is created.

fileRotationMb.description: The maximum file size to be saved in the bucket.

path.description: Path inside the Cloud Storage bucket to write data to.

endTime.description: Output only. The time the operation finished running.

requestedCancellation.description: Output only. Identifies whether the user has requested cancellation of the operation. Operations that have successfully been cancelled have Operation.error value with a google.rpc.Status.code of 1, corresponding to `Code.CANCELLED`.

apiVersion.description: Output only. API version used to start the operation.

target.description: Output only. Server-defined resource path for the target of the operation.

validationResult.description: Output only. Results of executed validations if there are any.

statusMessage.description: Output only. Human-readable status of the operation, if any.

createTime.description: Output only. The time the operation was created.

verb.description: Output only. Name of the verb executed by the operation.

OperationMetadata.description: Represents the metadata of the long-running operation.

locations.description: A list of locations that matches the specified filter in the request.
